Title: Elbow plank
Desc: The elbow plank is a popular isometric abdominal exercise. It targets the muscles of the core, the deep core or transversus abdominis in particular.

Title: Bottoms Up
Desc: The lying leg lift is a popular bodyweight exercise targeting the muscles of the abs, the rectus abdominis or “six-pack” muscles in particular.

Title: Spider crawl
Desc: The spider crawl is a bodyweight exercise that involves crawling on the floor with the knees outside of the elbows. It can be done as a full-body warm-up.

Title: Cocoons
Desc: The cocoon crunch is a bodyweight exercise targeting the ab muscles, involving bringing your knees to your chest and your arms from overhead to center.

Title: Cross-Body Crunch
Desc: The elbow-to-knee crunch is a bodyweight exercise targeting the ab muscles, the obliques and rectus abdominis in particular.

Title: Decline Crunch
Desc: The decline crunch is an effective core exercise targeting the rectus abdominis, performed on a decline bench.

Title: Hanging toes-to-bar
Desc: The hanging toes-to-bar is an advanced abdominal exercise in which the lifter touches their feet to a pull-up bar.

Title: Hanging Oblique Knee Raise
Desc: An abdominal exercise that targets both the rectus abdominus and the oblique muscles while hanging from a bar.

Title: Hanging leg raise
Desc: The hanging leg raise is an exercise targeting the abs, but which also works the lats and hip flexors.

Title: Mountain climber
Desc: A popular bodyweight exercise targeting the core, shoulders, and hips. It involves lifting one knee to the chest at a time from a plank position.

Title: Ab bicycle
Desc: A bodyweight movement that targets the muscles of the abs, the obliques and rectus abdominis in particular through a pedaling motion.

Title: 3/4 sit-up
Desc: Similar to a sit-up, but stops short of the top position. This keeps constant tension on the abs, making it more difficult.

Title: Reverse crunch
Desc: Popular exercise targeting the abdominals, particularly the lower half. It involves pulling the knees toward the chest.

Title: Dead bug reach
Desc: Exercise for strengthening the core in which you alternate lowering your opposing arm and leg simultaneously.

Title: V-up
Desc: A bodyweight movement that targets the muscles of the abs. It involves lifting the torso and legs to meet in a V-shape.

Title: Russian twist
Desc: Exercise targeting the abdominals and the obliques. It involves twisting side to side from a seated position.

Title: Flat Bench Lying Leg Raise
Desc: A popular bodyweight exercise targeting the muscles of the abs, particularly the lower rectus abdominis.

Title: Knees tucked crunch
Desc: A core exercise that involves performing a crunch while keeping the knees bent in a 90-degree position.

Title: Feet-elevated oblique crunch
Desc: Variation on the crunch that targets the obliques by resting the feet on a bench to focus stress on the abs.

Title: Bent-knee reverse crunch
Desc: A popular bodyweight core exercise that targets the lower portion of the rectus abdominis.

Title: Alternating heel-touch
Desc: Bodyweight exercise that targets the obliques by reaching side-to-side to touch the heels.

Title: Side Bridge
Desc: The side plank is a popular isometric abdominal exercise focusing on the oblique muscles and stability.

Title: Lying oblique crunch
Desc: The lying oblique crunch is a bodyweight exercise targeting the oblique muscles while lying on the side.

Title: Toe Touchers
Desc: A bodyweight movement that targets the rectus abdominis by reaching up to touch the toes while lying on the back.

Title: Shoulder tap
Desc: Exercise targeting the abdominals and core. From a plank position, one hand is raised to tap its opposing shoulder.

Title: Double crunch
Desc: Bodyweight exercise involving crunching the knees and elbows toward each other simultaneously using the abs.

Title: Flutter kick
Desc: Core exercise where the legs are held off the ground as you flutter your feet in small motions.

Title: Plank leg raise
Desc: Isometric abdominal exercise that targets the core and glutes by raising a leg during a plank.

Title: Reach crunch
Desc: A core exercise that involves keeping the arms raised toward the ceiling while performing a crunch.

Title: Hollow-body rock
Desc: Starts with a hollow-body hold and adds a back-and-forth rock that challenges core stability.

Title: Plank walk-out
Desc: From a standing position, the lifter walks the hands forward until they are out in front of the head.

Title: Seated leg lift
Desc: A bodyweight exercise targeting the muscles of the core and hip flexors while in a seated position.

Title: Knee-in to V-out
Desc: Abdominal exercise that primarily targets the rectus abdominis by combining a knee-in and leg extension.

Title: Plank reach
Desc: An exercise targeting the entire core, particularly the obliques, by reaching forward while in a plank.

Title: Plank up-down
Desc: Transitioning between elbow plank and straight-arm plank to put more stress on the triceps and core.

Title: Frog kick
Desc: An explosive bodyweight movement hopping the rear legs forward from a plank position.

Title: Cross-body mountain climber
Desc: Popular exercise where you bring the knee to the opposite side of the body while in a plank.

Title: Barbell floor wiper
Desc: Core exercise rotating hips and legs side to side, often performed with a barbell for stability.

Title: Hollow-body knee tuck
Desc: Combines a hollow-body hold and a knee tuck to target the rectus abdominis muscles.

Title: Active hang from bar
Desc: Static exercise involving isometrically activating the muscles of the upper back and core while hanging.

Title: Bodyweight squat
Desc: A fundamental exercise that strengthens the quads, glutes, and hamstrings.

Title: Forward lunge
Desc: A lower-body bodyweight exercise targeting the quads, glutes, and hamstrings.

Title: Reverse lunge
Desc: Targets the quads, glutes, and hamstrings, with more emphasis on the glutes than forward lunges.

Title: Walking lunge
Desc: Lower-body exercise that targets the glutes, quads, and hamstrings while challenging balance.

Title: Side-to-side box skip
Desc: Explosive lower-body exercise jumping laterally over a bench or box. Cardiovascular challenge.

Title: Broad jump
Desc: An explosive lower-body exercise measuring explosive hip and leg strength.

Title: Jump squat
Desc: An explosive bodyweight exercise targeting the quads, hamstrings, and glutes.

Title: Split Jump
Desc: Explosive bodyweight exercise that targets the lower-body muscles including quads and glutes.

Title: Step-up with knee raise
Desc: Lower-body exercise targeting the quads and glutes with a powerful hip flexion finish.

Title: Glute bridge
Desc: Popular lower-body exercise primarily targeting the glutes, lower back, and hamstrings.

Title: Single-leg glute bridge
Desc: A unilateral version of the glute bridge targeting the glutes and hamstrings on one side.

Title: Curtsy lunge
Desc: Bodyweight movement that targets the muscles of the hips and glutes with a crossing motion.

Title: Bulgarian Split Squat
Desc: Single-leg exercise targeting the quads, glutes, and hamstrings with the back leg elevated.

Title: Wall sit
Desc: An exercise targeting the quadriceps and core, involving holding a squat position against a wall.

Title: High knees
Desc: A full-body, cardio-based exercise with an emphasis on the lower body.

Title: Lateral lunge
Desc: A lower-body movement that works the quads, glutes, and hamstrings in a lateral plane.

Title: Pop squat
Desc: Explosive exercise targeting lower-body muscles, alternating narrow and wide stances.

Title: Speed skater
Desc: Explosive version of the lateral lunge jumping from side to side on a single leg.

Title: Tuck Jump
Desc: Vertical jump where the knees are pulled to the chest. Measures explosive power.

Title: Pigeon stretch
Desc: Lower-body stretch targeting the glutes, hips, and piriformis. Common in yoga.

Title: Single-leg box squat
Desc: Single-leg squat targeting the quads and glutes using a box to control depth.

Title: Lateral shuffle
Desc: Common sports training exercise involving quick lateral steps to each side.

Title: Bootstrapper squat
Desc: Movement that improves mobility, strength, and flexibility in the hips and hamstrings.

Title: Wall squat
Desc: Exercise targeting the quads and core by sliding the back against a wall.

Title: Single-leg knee-tap squat
Desc: Intense strength and coordination challenge involving a single-leg squat.

Title: Pushups
Desc: Classic upper-body movement to build muscle and strength in the chest, triceps, and shoulders.

Title: Incline Push-Up
Desc: Hands-elevated push-up variation that makes the exercise easier and shifts focus to the lower chest.

Title: Decline Push-Up
Desc: Feet-elevated push-up variation that increases difficulty and targets the upper chest and shoulders.

Title: Close-Hands Push-Up
Desc: Push-up variation that places more emphasis on the triceps and inner chest.

Title: Wide Push-Up
Desc: Push-up variation with hands wider than shoulder-width, targeting the chest more heavily.

Title: Diamond push-up
Desc: Advanced variation of the push-up targeting the triceps with hands in a diamond shape.

Title: Plyo push-up
Desc: Bodyweight exercise aimed at increasing upper-body power, strength, and explosiveness.

Title: Spider-man push-up
Desc: Variation involving pulling the knee to the elbow during the descent of a push-up.

Title: Typewriter push-up
Desc: Advanced push-up variation moving side-to-side at the bottom of a wide push-up position.

Title: Sphinx push-up
Desc: Difficult push-up variation ending on the forearms to place more stress on the triceps.

Title: Bench dip
Desc: Effective exercise for building the triceps by lowering the hips with hands on a bench.

Title: Triceps dip
Desc: Bodyweight exercise performed on parallel bars targeting the triceps, chest, and shoulders.

Title: Ring dip
Desc: Upper-body strength exercise on gymnastic rings targeting the chest, triceps, and shoulders.

Title: Scapular push-up
Desc: Upper-body exercise aimed at increasing scapular stability and shoulder mobility.

Title: Hand-release push-up
Desc: Variation where hands are momentarily lifted off the ground at the bottom of the rep.

Title: Pullups
Desc: Multi-joint bodyweight exercise that builds strength in the upper back, biceps, and core.

Title: Chin-Up
Desc: Variation of the pull-up with palms facing toward the body, utilizing the biceps more.

Title: Neutral-grip pull-up
Desc: Multi-joint bodyweight exercise performed with palms facing one another for shoulder health.

Title: Inverted Row
Desc: Bodyweight exercise targeting the lats and upper back by pulling toward a bar while hanging.

Title: Handstand push-up
Desc: Advanced exercise targeting the shoulders, performed in a vertical handstand position.

Title: Wall walk
Desc: Challenging exercise where hands walk back and feet walk up a wall to a handstand.

Title: Bear crawl
Desc: Intense full-body movement targeting the cardiovascular system, shoulders, core, and legs.

Title: Superman
Desc: Isometric hold in an extended spine position targeting the glutes, erectors, and upper back.

Title: Bird dog
Desc: Core exercise designed to strengthen and stabilize the posterior chain and core.

Title: Arm circle
Desc: Non-weighted exercise targeting the shoulders, used commonly for warm-ups.

Title: Back extension
Desc: Exercise used to build lower back strength that also targets the hamstrings and glutes.

Title: Inchworm
Desc: Bodyweight exercise involving walking the hands out to a plank and back to a toe-touch.

Title: Y-T-W raises
Desc: Upper-body movements that target the shoulders and postural muscles of the back.

Title: Burpee
Desc: High-intensity exercise that recruits the entire body to build strength and aerobic capacity.

Title: Sprawl
Desc: Explosive bodyweight exercise that targets the core, upper body, and lower body.

Title: Crab walk
Desc: Full-body exercise that is a coordination challenge and burns serious calories.

Title: Side kick-through
Desc: Full-body movement starting in a bear crawl position and kicking a leg out to the side.

Title: Jumping jack
Desc: Classic calisthenics exercise used to improve overall conditioning and heart rate.

Title: Shadow boxing
Desc: Exercise typically used in combat sports, excellent for cardio and active rest.

Title: World's greatest stretch
Desc: Popular movement targeting multiple parts of the body including hips and thoracic spine.
